label.value: immature protein part

value.value: A part of a protein that is removed during the protein maturation process.

value.value: An immature protein part that is the N-terminal most residue.

definition.value: The initiator methionine is cleaved co-translationally. For this reason, we do not use the derives_from relation when defining protein forms lacking the initiator (because the precursor form does not yet exist at the time of removal).

label.value: cholera enterotoxin subunit A1

value.value: A cholera enterotoxin subunit A isoform 1 that has been processed by proteolytic cleavage to yield the catalytic subunit of subunit A. The cholera holotoxin consists of a pentameric ring of B subunits whose central pore is occupied by the A subunit. The A subunit contains two chains, A1 and A2, linked by a disulfide bridge.
